From 72f0aa968d3dd53bbb0e399ef911d593b3dc1c31 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 18:09:15 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] chronium: skip TLS Trust Anchor IDs extension (0xCA34) for
 JA4 parity with Chrome stable
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The dev build was emitting an extra ClientHello extension at codepoint
0xCA34 (TLSEXT_TYPE_trust_anchors) with empty data 0x0000, shifting JA4
from t13d1516h2 (Chrome stable) to t13d1517h2 (dev build) and changing
both the JA4 and peetprint hashes. That mismatch alone is enough for
Cloudflare Bot Management Premium (grok.com) to refuse the connection
regardless of how good the in-browser fingerprint patches are.

Root cause: features::kTLSTrustAnchorIDs is FEATURE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT,
but ssl_config_.trust_anchor_ids ends up an empty-valued optional through
the DNS service-endpoint path, so the has_value() check at line 849 fires
and BoringSSL serializes the extension with a zero-length body. Real
Chrome on the same tag stays at nullopt for this field on typical hosts.

Fix: cut the SSL_set1_requested_trust_anchors call at the TCP/HTTP-2
site. (Companion QUIC site at
net/third_party/quiche/src/quiche/quic/core/tls_client_handshaker.cc
lives in a submodule and is patched separately in the working tree.)

Verified after rebuild via https://tls.peet.ws/api/all (no sidecar,
no proxy, direct from chronium.exe):
  ja4                      t13d1516h2_8daaf6152771_d8a2da3f94cd  (Chrome 149 stable)
  akamai_fingerprint_hash  52d84b11737d980aef856699f885ca86      (matches)
  peetprint_hash           1d4ffe9b0e34acac0bd883fa7f79d7b5      (matches)
  Unknown extension 51764  GONE
  ja4_r ext list           ...0033,44cd,fe0d,ff01 (16 ext, ca34 removed)

This eliminates the need for the curl_cffi mitmproxy sidecar on most
paths — chronium can go direct and still pass standard Cloudflare gates.
Sidecar remains useful for chaining residential/mobile proxies for
IP-reputation-gated sites.
---
 net/socket/ssl_client_socket_impl.cc | 30 +++++++++++++++-------------
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/socket/ssl_client_socket_impl.cc b/net/socket/ssl_client_socket_impl.cc
index 8ac44772109a8..279997ea6b787 100644
--- a/net/socket/ssl_client_socket_impl.cc
+++ b/net/socket/ssl_client_socket_impl.cc
@@ -845,20 +845,22 @@ int SSLClientSocketImpl::Init() {
 
   SSL_set_permute_extensions(ssl_.get(), 1);
 
-  // Configure BoringSSL to send Trust Anchor IDs, if provided.
-  if (ssl_config_.trust_anchor_ids.has_value()) {
-    if (!SSL_set1_requested_trust_anchors(
-            ssl_.get(), ssl_config_.trust_anchor_ids->data(),
-            ssl_config_.trust_anchor_ids->size())) {
-      return ERR_UNEXPECTED;
-    }
-    net_log_.AddEvent(NetLogEventType::SSL_CLIENT_TRUST_ANCHOR_IDS_LIST, [&] {
-      return base::DictValue().Set(
-          "trust_anchor_ids",
-          x509_util::TrustAnchorIDsToString(x509_util::ParseTlsTrustAnchorIDs(
-              *ssl_config_.trust_anchor_ids)));
-    });
-  }
+  // Chronium: NEVER send the TLS Trust Anchor IDs extension (0xCA34 /
+  // TLSEXT_TYPE_trust_anchors). Real Chrome stable on this same tag does
+  // not emit it for typical HTTPS hosts; our dev build calls
+  // SSL_set1_requested_trust_anchors with an empty list anyway, which
+  // makes BoringSSL emit `extension(0xCA34) data=0000`. That extra byte
+  // pair turns up in JA4 as `ca34` and shifts the JA4 hash off the real
+  // Chrome value — Cloudflare Bot Management Premium (grok.com) refuses
+  // the connection on that mismatch alone. Drop the call wholesale; we
+  // don't rely on server-side trust anchor selection in any of the
+  // protected workflows.
+  // Original guarded block kept commented for diff-tracking against
+  // upstream:
+  //   if (ssl_config_.trust_anchor_ids.has_value()) {
+  //     if (!SSL_set1_requested_trust_anchors(...)) return ERR_UNEXPECTED;
+  //     net_log_.AddEvent(...);
+  //   }
 
   // The compliance policy must be the last thing configured in order to have
   // defined behavior.
-- 
2.54.0.windows.1

